---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Allianz Care in France', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-coverage', text: 'Pre-PUMA Visa Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'france-network', text: 'Network Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'vs-local-options', text: 'vs French Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'claims', text: 'Using Your Insurance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose Allianz', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in France', href: '/countries/france/insurance' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Allianz vs Cigna', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'francePrice', header: 'France (Age 40)' },
  { key: 'deductible', header: 'Deductible Option' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Essential', coverage: 'Inpatient + Emergency', francePrice: '€100-140/mo', deductible: 'Up to €5,000' },
  { plan: 'Classic', coverage: 'Essential + Outpatient', francePrice: '€160-210/mo', deductible: 'Up to €5,000' },
  { plan: 'Premium', coverage: 'Comprehensive', francePrice: '€210-280/mo', deductible: 'Up to €5,000' },
  { plan: 'Platinum', coverage: 'Premium + Enhanced', francePrice: '€260-350/mo', deductible: 'Up to €5,000' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'french', header: 'French System' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { factor: 'Monthly Cost (Age 40)', allianz: '€160-210', french: '€50-150 (mutuelle)' },
  { factor: 'With High Deductible', allianz: '€70-110', french: 'N/A' },
  { factor: 'Pre-PUMA Coverage', allianz: 'Full coverage', french: 'Not available' },
  { factor: 'Coverage Outside France', allianz: 'Worldwide', french: 'EU (EHIC) only' },
  { factor: 'Deductible Savings', allianz: 'Up to 60%', french: 'No option' },
  { factor: 'EU Insurer', allianz: 'Yes (German)', french: 'Yes (French)' },
  { factor: 'Portability', allianz: 'Worldwide', french: 'France only' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Allianz Care Health Insurance in France"
  description="Complete guide to using Allianz Care in France. High-deductible savings, visa coverage, and comparison to the French healthcare system."
  headline="Allianz Care Health Insurance in France"
  subheadline="EU-based international coverage for expats in France. High-deductible savings and pre-PUMA visa coverage."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/france-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Allianz France Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/allianz-care"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Allianz Care in France</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers international coverage for expats in France with a standout feature: high-deductible options that can cut premiums by up to 60%. As an EU-based insurer (German), Allianz may have advantages when dealing with French authorities.
  </p>
  <p>
    Like all international insurance in France, Allianz serves two purposes: coverage during the pre-PUMA period, and ongoing worldwide coverage for expats who travel or may relocate.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">2M+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Providers worldwide</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">60%</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Max deductible savings</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">EU</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Based and regulated</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a France-Specific Quote"
    description="See what Allianz Care costs with different deductible options."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/allianz-care"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="visa-coverage">Pre-PUMA Visa Coverage</h2>
  <p>
    For French long-stay visa applications, you need private health insurance. PUMA enrollment takes 3+ months after establishing residency.
  </p>

  <h3>Visa Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Comprehensive inpatient and outpatient coverage</li>
    <li>Valid for the full visa duration</li>
    <li>Adequate coverage limits</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Allianz Care Classic, Premium, and Platinum plans meet these requirements. As an EU insurer, French consulates may be familiar with Allianz documentation.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">EU Insurer Advantage</h3>
    <p class="text-green-800">
      As an EU-based insurer, Allianz Care is regulated within the European framework. This can simplify interactions with French authorities and may provide additional confidence for visa applications.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="france-network">Network Coverage in France</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care has a good network in France with direct billing at major private hospitals.
  </p>

  <h3>Key Network Points</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Paris:</strong> Coverage including American Hospital of Paris</li>
    <li><strong>Major cities:</strong> Network in Lyon, Nice, Bordeaux, Marseille</li>
    <li><strong>EU-wide:</strong> Seamless coverage across Europe</li>
    <li><strong>Reimbursement:</strong> Any licensed French provider</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices for worldwide coverage excluding USA. High deductibles (€2,500-5,000) reduce premiums by 40-60%.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>The High-Deductible Strategy</h3>
  <p>
    Once you have PUMA, a high-deductible Allianz plan makes sense: PUMA covers routine care, Allianz covers major expenses beyond the deductible. This maximizes savings while maintaining worldwide coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Which Plan for France?</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Classic:</strong> The balanced choice. Meets visa requirements, covers outpatient.</li>
    <li><strong>Premium:</strong> Enhanced benefits. Good for comprehensive coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Platinum:</strong> Maximum coverage for those wanting the best.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Calculate Your Savings"
    description="See how different deductible options affect your premium."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/allianz-care"
  />

  <h2 id="vs-local-options">vs French Options</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Keep Allianz Care If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You're in the pre-PUMA period</li>
    <li>You want high-deductible savings</li>
    <li>You travel within Europe frequently</li>
    <li>You might relocate from France</li>
    <li>You prefer an EU-regulated insurer</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Switch to PUMA + Mutuelle If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You're staying in France long-term</li>
    <li>You don't travel outside the EU much</li>
    <li>Budget is a concern</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    <a href="/countries/france/insurance">See all France insurance options →</a>
  </p>

  <h2 id="claims">Using Your Insurance in France</h2>

  <h3>Direct Billing</h3>
  <p>
    At network hospitals, show your Allianz card for cashless treatment.
  </p>

  <h3>Reimbursement</h3>
  <p>
    For non-network providers, pay and submit via the MyHealth app. French factures are accepted without translation.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose Allianz in France</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Budget-conscious (high-deductible strategy)</li>
        <li>Expats who travel within Europe</li>
        <li>Those who prefer EU-based insurers</li>
        <li>Pre-PUMA visa applicants</li>
        <li>People who might relocate</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Long-term France residents (PUMA + mutuelle)</li>
        <li>Those wanting English hospital access (Cigna)</li>
        <li>Expats who don't travel much</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>How does the high-deductible work with PUMA?</h3>
  <p>
    After PUMA enrollment, PUMA covers routine care. A high-deductible Allianz plan covers major expenses beyond your deductible and worldwide travel. This combination provides comprehensive coverage at lower cost.
  </p>

  <h3>Is Allianz Care accepted for French visas?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, Allianz Care Classic and higher plans are typically accepted. Verify with your consulate.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I move within Europe?</h3>
  <p>
    Your coverage continues unchanged. Simply update your residence with Allianz.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Coverage in France?"
    description="Get a personalized Allianz Care quote with deductible options."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/allianz-care"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Visa requirements and PUMA rules change. Verify all information with Allianz Care and French authorities.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
